🚗 Vehicle Detection and Counting Using YOLO & OpenCV
📌 Project Overview

This project implements a real-time Vehicle Detection and Counting System using the YOLO (You Only Look Once) object detection algorithm and OpenCV. The system identifies vehicles present in an image, draws bounding boxes around detected vehicles, and calculates the total vehicle count.

The model filters only vehicle-related classes and ignores other detected objects, making it useful for traffic monitoring, smart city applications, and transportation analytics.
